            <div type="translation" resp="part:reda part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1"> 		
                    Hail! Prosperity!
                </p>
                
                <p n="1-4">
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">I</supplied>, Dhanmaputtiraṉ, have given the land to the Lord Nalla-Nāyaṉar of Nallūr the <supplied reason="subaudible">following</supplied> endowment to cover the requierements of temple worship <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>arccana-bhoga</foreign></supplied>:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <list>
                        <item>360 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s including the raised mound <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>mēṭum</foreign></supplied> surrounding the four boundaries of Nallūr and the nine ponds for the Navagrahas <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>navakkiraka kuḷam oṉpatum</foreign></supplied>,</item>
                        <item>5 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s of land for the sacred garden on the northern bank of the river, and </item>
                        <item>5 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s of land from the village Kāccuvakuṭi</item> 
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p n="10-12">
                    The land amounting to 370 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s of land have been given to the Lord Nalla Nāyaṉār.
                </p>
                <p n="12-13">
                    This is under the protection of the <foreign>paṉmaheśvara</foreign>s.
                </p>
                
            </div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>
                    This record continues <ref target="DHARMA_INSTamilNadu00031.xml"/>. Given that the present inscription is carved after this early record and <ref target="DHARMA_INSTamilNadu00032.xml"/> and the three of them seem to be part of the same administrative dossier, this one may be the summary of the previous ones.
                </p>
                </div>
            
